
MENU. Select a box or folder by pointing to it and pressing the LEFT mouse but-
ton.  Use the RIGHT mouse button to cancel and the [HELP] key for advice at any
time. The VOICE box will be used for spoken stories. 
      Use "Start" to create a new drawing, which will be stored on the RAM disc
'D'   as  a file,  when it has been  given  a  title (files are drawings).  Use
"Redraw" to alter an old file,  which is then stored on 'D'.  A seris of  files
should be kept together in a folder.  To create a folder, click on "Folder" and
type in a name;  then press [RETURN]. The name will appear under FOLDERS. Click
on the name and it will replace the  'A'  directory and list its contents.
You  can move a file from 'D' into a folder on 'A'  or onto the  'A'  directory
itself.
      Use "Transfer" to move files from 'A' to 'D' or back.  In transferring or
deleting  files,  point to the file.  Pointing to the folder on 'A' or 'D' will
cause  ALL files to be transferred. Deletions will require confirmation.
      Use the RETURN box or the RIGHT mouse button to change discs or to  start
again. 
       For  Animation,   create  a  series  of  drawings  on  'D',   ending  in
consecutive numbers -  from 1 to 9 and then from A up  to I. For speech, or for
reading, make the folder's name end in a number.  
                                                      Now press the [SPACE BAR]
